{
  "title": "SWOT–AHP & TOWS Strategy Analyzer: Browser-based tool for robust strategic prioritization with bootstrap uncertainty quantification",
  "description": "<p>A self-contained browser-based and Python tool implementing a complete SWOT–AHP (A'WOT) analytical pipeline for strategic planning. Features include: (1) AHP eigenvector-based prioritization with Saaty consistency diagnostics, (2) geometric mean aggregation of group judgments, (3) two-level multiplicative global weight synthesis, (4) multi-scenario sensitivity analysis under four quadrant-weight postures, (5) respondent-level nonparametric bootstrap resampling with rank acceptability probabilities and percentile confidence intervals, (6) TOWS strategy matrix translation, and (7) Strategy Priority Index (SPI) ranking with bootstrap uncertainty. Designed for conservation education, natural resource management, and related strategic planning applications. All computation runs client-side with no data upload.</p>",
  "creators": [
    {
      "name": "Kharel, Gehendra",
      "affiliation": "Texas Christian University",
